Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil your #kettle{}.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@olive oil{}, then sprinkle the @lemon & herb seasoning{1} onto the fish, coating the
top and sides. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Meanwhile, trim and discard the root and dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}.
Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Pour the @boiled water for the risotto{450%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Add the
@vegetable stock paste{20%g} and stir well to combine - this is your veg stock.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an
> ovenproof dish before baking.

Once the #ovenproof pan{} is hot, add the leek and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the garlic and @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the
rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in your veg stock. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan
(or cover with #foil{}).

Bake on the middle shelf of your #oven{} until the rice is cooked and the water has
been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When the risotto has 15 mins left, roast the salmon on the top shelf of your oven
until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1}(zested and halved). Pick the @mint{1%bunch} leaves
from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

In a #medium bowl{}, squeeze in some lemon juice. Mix in the chopped mint, @salt{},
@pepper{}, @honey{1}, and @olive oil for the dressing{2%tbsp}.

Pop the courgette ribbons into the dressing and toss to coat.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @peas{120%g},
lemon zest, @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated) and @butter{20%g}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

When everything's ready, share the pea risotto between your #bowls{}.

Serve the marinated courgette ribbons on top to one side and the salmon on the
other.

Toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} through the remaining dressing in the bowl and serve
alongside.

Enjoy!